The paper deals with the problem of simultaneous multicasting of multiple messages with the help of a relay terminal, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also presents achievable rate regions for the cMACr model based on decode-and-forward (DF) and compress-and-forward (CF) relaying strategies, which are relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the benefits of physical layer network coding and structured codes, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer communications (cs.COM).
